  "content": [
    {
      "type": "header",
      "level": 1,
      "text": "Clinical Setting"
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "items": [
        "Pericarditis associated with histoplasmosis in most cases is not due to direct infection but instead due to inflammation of adjacent mediastinal lymph nodes."
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "header",
      "level": 1,
      "text": "Etiologies"
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "items": [
        "Histoplasma capsulatum"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "header",
      "level": 1,
      "text": "Primary Regimens"
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "items": [
        "Mild symptoms: Nonsteroidal anti-inflammatory drug (NSAID) therapy"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "nestedContent",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "NSAID non-responders or hemodynamic compromise:"
        },
        {
          "type": "regimen",
          "regimenData": {
            "intent": "treatment",
            "components": [
              {
                "drug": "Prednisone",
                "dose": "1 mg/kg",
                "route": "po",
                "frequency": "daily tapered over 1-2 weeks"
              },
              {
                "drug": "Itraconazole",
                "dose": "200 mg",
                "route": "po",
                "frequency": "3 times daily x 3 days and then twice daily x 6-12 weeks",
                "connector": "+"
              }
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "list",
          "items": [
            "Pericardial fluid removal for hemodynamic compromise"
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "header",
      "level": 1,
      "text": "Alternative Regimens"
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "items": [
        "None"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "header",
      "level": 1,
